    <div class="text-container">
      <p>bookeasy.online came from real journeys and years of hands-on experience.</p>
      <p>
        The founder spent years guiding and assisting travelers in
        <strong>Azerbaijan, Turkey, and Japan</strong>, working closely with international guests.
        Over time, she kept hearing the same frustrations:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>“Booking sites are too complicated.”</li>
        <li>“Email chains take forever.”</li>
        <li>“I still struggled at the restaurant because of the language barrier.”</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        So she created the very solution her customers wished existed — one that has a
        <strong>clean, simple interface</strong>,
        <strong>clear and easy-to-understand communication</strong>, and
        <strong>real human support</strong> — even during the meal if needed.
      </p>
    </div>
